Banaras Itinerary Details⬇️🤩

We stayed for 20 Days - 💸15k per person including everything!
STAY OPTION - Teerth Guest House, near Dashashwmedh ghat! Best in safety & hospitality✨✌️

⬇️Day 1:

Start your day with a Ganga Snan in the morning.
Visit Kal Bhairav Temple for blessings.
End the day with Ganga Aarti at Dashashwamedh Ghat (7:30 PM).❣️🤩

⬇️Day 2:

Morning Boat Ride: ₹800/hour 🛶

Food Walk:😋
1️⃣ Shri Satyanarayan Sweets:
Kachori Sabzi: ₹50 (Best)
Chinne ka Dahi Wada: ₹30 (Masterpiece)

2️⃣ Shri Ji Sweets & Milk:
Malaiyo: ₹50 (Heavenly 💕)

3️⃣ Pehalwan Lassi:
Badi Lassi: ₹60 (Skip Blue Lassi❌)

4️⃣ Baati Chokha Restaurant:
Sattu Baati: ₹30, Paneer Baati: ₹30
Chokha (Full): ₹160, Churma: ₹65

5️⃣ Hidden Gem (Name unknown):
Malai Lassi: ₹40 (Our Fave 💯)

6️⃣ Deepak Tambul Bhandar:
Banarasi Sweet Paan: ₹50

Evening: Visit Manikarnika Ghat for a spiritual experience (at your own risk).

⬇️Day 3:

Early Morning Ganga Aarti: Assi Ghat (5:30 AM) 🌅
Temple Visits: Kedareshwar, Sankat Mochan, and Annapurna Temples.
Night Highlight: Don’t miss the 10:30 PM Aarti at Shri Kashi Vishwanath Temple! Goosebumps guaranteed!⚡️

Share this reel with your friends & plan your budget-friendly trip with @skyscanner.india 🧳✈️

Itinerary Details ⬇️🏔️

Total Trip Budget (1 Month): ₹25k per person (including food, travel, and stay)✨

Dal Lake: Take a Shikara ride to explore this stunning lake, visiting Golden Lake, Mina Bazaar, Floating Garden, and Gulfam Lake. Cost: ₹800-1000.🛶

Doodhpathri: Rent a bike in Srinagar for ₹800-1000/day and ride through one of Kashmir’s most beautiful valleys. Rental shop details are in the itinerary PDF.🌄🏕️

Pahalgam: No Kashmir trip is complete without Pahalgam! Experience authentic Kashmiri culture. Take a local train from Srinagar to Anantnag, then a shared taxi to Pahalgam village.❣️🏞️

Tulian Lake: Visit in summer to see the true beauty of Tulian Lake. A 1-day moderate trek will get you there but will suggest you take a camping stop in Tulian Valley to witness one of Kashmir’s best sunsets.❣️✨

For more details, comment “Kashmir” and we’ll send you the itinerary PDF for free.🌄❣️

Darjeeling Food Walk Details🍽️🚂

1️⃣ Glenary’s Cafe – This is the oldest & most iconic café in town. Thoda expensive hai but the Big Breakfast is a must try Aur haan, photos ke liye toh perfect spot hai! 📸

2️⃣ Tom & Jerry Cafe – Budget-friendly & super cute! Aise pancakes aapko pure Darjeeling mein kahi nahi milenge 🥞 Totally worth every penny!

3️⃣ Dekevas Cafe – Tibetan, Korean & Chinese food lovers, this is your place! Momos toh must hai, but Dragon Chicken Bao stole our hearts 🔥

4️⃣ Kathmandu Kitchen – Our absolute favourite! Nepali vibes, amazing aesthetics & don’t you dare miss the Nepali pizza – it’s crunchy, cheesy & totally unique 🍕🇳🇵

📍All these cafés are around Mall Road, easy to find & totally worth visiting.

Manebhanjan — Land of Land Rover’s😍

Just 23 km from Darjeeling, this hidden gem sits right on the India-Nepal border.
Yaha chalte chalte hi Nepal cross kar jaoge! 🇮🇳🇳🇵

Vintage Land Rovers are not museum pieces here — they are daily taxis 🚕
Truly, Incredible India! 🌏

🚂 Toy Train (Steam Engine): ₹1500 (Darjeeling–Ghum)

🏍️ Bike Rental: ₹800/bike
👉 Dreams Tour & Hospitality: 
+91 9382891407

🌲 Manebhanjan Land Rover Ride: ₹2500/jeep (Manebhanjan - Chitre - Meghma - Tumling)

🍽️ DARJEELING FOOD WALK 🍽️

1️⃣ Glenary’s Cafe – Iconic & aesthetic! Big Breakfast is a must-try. 📸

2️⃣ Tom & Jerry Cafe – Budget-friendly pancakes that’ll blow your mind! 🥞

3️⃣ Dekevas Cafe – For Tibetan, Korean, Chinese food cravings. Try the Dragon Chicken Bao! 🔥

4️⃣ Kathmandu Kitchen – Our absolute fav! Don’t miss the crunchy Nepali pizza 🍕🇳🇵
